title: Monitor replay-to-live handoff can drop a newly appended event
updated_at: "2026-07-19T09:43:27Z"
---
hark monitor performs replay_matching() and follow_state_files() as separate phases. If a matching record is appended after replay_matching has read the files but before StateFeedFollower.start_live(), start_live seeks to the current EOF and the record is neither replayed nor emitted live. Deterministic review repro on B140 inserted an append at that boundary: the record remained durably present in ambient.jsonl but monitor output was empty for it. This behavior predates B140. Acceptance: subscribe/establish a durable cursor before replay or perform a lossless catch-up handoff; prove with a deterministic boundary append regression for replay>0 and preserve rotation/truncation handling.